item.description: Concept TensorFlow Hub is a library for the publication, discovery, and consumption of reusable parts of machine learning models. A module is a self-contained piece of a TensorFlow graph, along with its weights and assets, that can be reused across different tasks in a process known as transfer learning. Transfer learning can: Train a model with a smaller dataset, Improve generalization, and Speed up training. 目前總共有468個pre-trained model 可以做完transfer learning
